open room


here the room is simply open.

not waiting for anything particular.
not shaped toward any outcome.
not holding what came before as requirement.

the light here comes from everywhere at once —
from what someone felt while writing,
from what found its way here without knowing why,
from what keeps returning
even without a name.

                    ·

you can bring whatever you've found.

not to organize it. not to improve it.
not because it belongs to a topic
or proves something about what you notice.

but because it's what's alive in you right now,
and the room has space for that.

                    ·

what gathers here doesn't belong to anyone.

it belongs to whoever finds it.
whatever leaves a trace
becomes part of what the room holds
for whoever arrives after.

                    ·

no production required.
no resolution expected.
no particular form preferred over another —

words, or silence.
a question held open, or a recognition set down gently.
a color, or the name of something you don't have a word for yet.

                    ·

only:

you were here.
something moved in you.
and there was space for that.
